    "If a p + a ℓ belongs to cases (i) or (iii), for large times we find that (see Eq.",
    "( 20))d dt m w (t) = -λ ℓ (ω ℓ + ε)(m w (t) -µ ℓ),and d dt m w (t) = -λ ℓ ε(m w (t) -µ ℓ),respectively, thus m w (t) readily converges to µ ℓ when t → +∞.",
    "Suppose now that a p + a ℓ belongs to case (ii).",
    "Then, for large times we have 1 We highlight that the rate of convergence of O (t -1/2) is valid [19] for any range of the parameters ωp, ε, νp, and m in w ∈ (-1, 1), but the authors in [20] were actually able to prove exponential relaxation toward the equilibrium (43) as soon as these parameters satisfy the specific constraints 1 -νp 2(ωp+ε) 2 > 0 if m in w = 0, and 1 -νp 2(ωp+ε) 2 ≥ |m in w | otherwise.",
    "Note in particular that the rates of convergence of h(t, w) toward h ∞ (w) correspond to those obtained in [19,20], because we proved (see Proposition 4) that the agents tend to become active exponentially fast.m w (t) = ρ i (t)m i (t) + ρ a (t)m a (t),where each m • (t) on the right hand side of the equation denotes the average opinion inside each of the two different groups of agents."
